The paper applies deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, to the task of decoding and visualizing EEG pathology. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests a focus on neural computation (cs.NE). The paper also involves image processing and analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the potential clinical applications of the research suggest a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
